1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Most AI tutors forget you when the conversation ends.
In every new session, you have to repeat your goals and preferences.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:16,000
WeakSpot is different. It is an English coach with persistent memory
that learns what works for each learner across sessions.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Here, I only submit a short piece of writing.
Qwen diagnoses the language and identifies durable information.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:32,500
In the same structured response,
it proposes durable memory candidates.

5
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:41,000
WeakSpot stores my communication goal, concise-feedback preference,
and evidenced grammar weaknesses.

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:48,000
No separate memory workflow
or additional model call is required.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:56,500
In a new session, WeakSpot does not send
the learner's entire history back to the model.

8
00:00:56,500 --> 00:01:05,000
Qwen text-embedding-v4 and lexical matching
retrieve the most relevant memories.

9
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:16,000
The final Memory Pack contains no more than six memories
and must fit inside a 700-token budget.

10
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:24,000
This is not an append-only transcript.
Equivalent observations are merged instead of duplicated.

11
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Conflicting evidence replaces the active fact,
and the previous version is archived as superseded.

12
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:39,000
The learner can inspect, correct, pin,
or forget any memory.

13
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:48,000
Every graded attempt updates strategy evidence
for a specific skill and exercise format.

14
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:58,000
WeakSpot combines mastery gap, error density, spacing,
historical performance, productive difficulty, and exploration.

15
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:07,000
The recommendation explains why it was selected
and links back to the supporting memories.

16
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:16,000
The FastAPI backend runs in Docker on Alibaba Cloud ECS.
Qwen 3.7 Max handles deep analysis and planning.

17
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Qwen 3.7 Plus handles faster workflows,
and text-embedding-v4 powers the hybrid memory ranker.

18
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:34,000
DynamoDB stores cross-session memory,
lifecycle metadata, and auditable recall traces.

19
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:44,000
The benchmark reaches 100% Recall at Six,
respects every token budget, and reduces context by 82.6%.

20
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:54,000
WeakSpot remembers not only your mistakes,
but your goals and how you learn best.
